        <h1>LeetCode 1653: Minimum Deletions to Make String Balanced (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a string s consisting only of characters 'a' and 'b'. A string is balanced if there is no
                pair of indices (i, j) such that i &lt; j and s[i] = 'b' and s[j] = 'a'. Return the minimum number of
                deletions needed to make s balanced.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "aababbab"<br>
                Output: 2<br>
                Explanation: Delete the two 'a's at positions 5 and 6 to get "aabbb", which is balanced. Alternatively,
                delete other characters, but 2 is minimum.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeletions(string s) {
        int res = 0, b = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == 'a')
                res = min(res + 1, b); // delete 'a' or all prior 'b'
            else
                b++;
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
